=================================================================
  Karatsuba: Serial vs OpenMP Parallel
  Threads          : 8
  Base threshold   : 32 digits  (switch to schoolbook)
  Task threshold   : 500 digits  (stop spawning OMP tasks)
=================================================================

--- Correctness (10 random pairs, varying sizes) ---
       7 digits: Serial==Parallel: PASS ✓
       9 digits: Serial==Parallel: PASS ✓
      50 digits: Serial==Parallel: PASS ✓
     100 digits: Serial==Parallel: PASS ✓
     500 digits: Serial==Parallel: PASS ✓
    1000 digits: Serial==Parallel: PASS ✓
    5000 digits: Serial==Parallel: PASS ✓
   10000 digits: Serial==Parallel: PASS ✓
   50000 digits: Serial==Parallel: PASS ✓
  100000 digits: Serial==Parallel: PASS ✓
  Overall: ALL PASSED ✓

--- Sample output (123456789 x 987654321) ---
  Serial  : 121932631112635269
  Parallel: 121932631112635269
  Match   : YES ✓

--- Benchmark (wall-clock time per single multiplication) ---

  Digits      Reps    Serial (s)      Parallel (s)    Speedup   
  ----------  ------  --------------  --------------  ----------
  9           100000  0.000000        0.000002        0.11x
  50          50000   0.000007        0.000013        0.54x
  100         10000   0.000024        0.000092        0.26x
  500         2000    0.000459        0.000362        1.27x
  1000        500     0.001198        0.001344        0.89x
  5000        20      0.016847        0.005112        3.30x
  10000       10      0.051145        0.016144        3.17x
  50000       5       0.725683        0.194382        3.73x
  100000      3       2.174379        0.659727        3.30x

  Speedup > 1.0x means OpenMP is faster than serial.
  Speedup < 1.0x means task overhead outweighs parallelism gain.
  (More threads = higher speedup at large digit counts)
